** Django

Start app with:

$ source venv/bin/activate
$ python childhealth/manage.py run_gunicorn


** Postgres

After installing a default postgres on Ubuntu, there is a postgres
user with no password.

See https://help.ubuntu.com/community/PostgreSQL#Create_database

$ sudo apt-get install postgresql
$ sudo -u postgres createdb childhealth_db

Create yourself a user:

$ sudo -u postgres createuser --superuser $USER


** pip

Install all the required packages:

$ pip install -r requirements.txt

See also http://www.pip-installer.org/en/latest/requirements.html.
